# Solution:
The function is supposed to iterate through each node in the directed graph and add nodes with no predecessors to an array list. However, the function is only adding the first node in the directed graph to the array list. The function is also adding nodes to the array list if the list of successors for that node is contained in the list of successors for another node in the array list. This means that the function is adding nodes with no predecessors to the array list but also nodes that are not actually a topological ordering of the directed graph.

The fix for this bug is to remove the check for if the list of successors for a node is contained in the list of successors for another node in the array list. This will ensure that the array list only contains nodes with no predecessors and will not add any nodes that are not a topological ordering of the directed graph.

